---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Germany Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/germany/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Austria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/austria' },
  { title: 'Switzerland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/switzerland' },
  { title: 'Netherlands for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/netherlands' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'germanyFit', header: 'Germany Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€320-450/mo', germanyFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€350-480/mo', germanyFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€420-600/mo', germanyFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€300-420/mo', germanyFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'German PKV (Private)', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€400-800/mo', germanyFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€320-480', annual: '€3,840-5,760' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€450-650', annual: '€5,400-7,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€600-900', annual: '€7,200-10,800' },
  { category: 'German GKV (Public)', monthly: '14.6% income', annual: 'Income-based' },
  { category: 'German PKV (Private)', monthly: '€400-800', annual: '€4,800-9,600' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Germany 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Germany. GKV vs PKV systems, visa requirements, Munich and Berlin hospitals, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Germany"
  subheadline="Germany offers exceptional healthcare, rich culture, and central European location—with both public and private insurance pathways for retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/germany-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Germany</h2>
  <p>
    Germany combines world-class healthcare, efficient infrastructure, and rich cultural offerings. For seniors, the country provides excellent medical care, safe cities, and easy access to the rest of Europe via high-speed rail and well-connected airports.
  </p>

  <p>
    Munich offers Bavarian charm with access to the Alps. Berlin provides vibrant culture at relatively affordable prices. Hamburg and Düsseldorf have strong expat communities. Smaller cities like Heidelberg and Freiburg offer historic charm with excellent healthcare access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> World-class; ranked top 15 globally</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> German essential; English common in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €2,000-3,500/month; Berlin more affordable than Munich</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Four seasons; cold winters, mild summers</li>
      <li><strong>Public Transport:</strong> Exceptional rail network (Deutsche Bahn, ICE trains)</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member; Schengen zone</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Germany's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Germany has a dual healthcare system: statutory public insurance (Gesetzliche Krankenversicherung/GKV) and private insurance (Private Krankenversicherung/PKV). About 90% of residents are in GKV, with higher earners and self-employed often choosing PKV.
  </p>

  <p>
    German hospitals are excellent, with many university hospitals ranking among Europe's best. Charité in Berlin is world-renowned. Wait times are generally shorter than in the UK or Canada. Most doctors in cities speak English, though German helps significantly.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">GKV vs PKV for Seniors</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Switching from PKV to GKV after age 55 is nearly impossible in Germany. If you've been privately insured, you'll typically stay private. GKV premiums are income-based (14.6%); PKV premiums are age/health-based and increase with age. Plan carefully before choosing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Germany offers several pathways for non-EU seniors:
  </p>

  <h3>Independent Means Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For financially independent retirees with sufficient pension income (typically €1,200-1,500/month) and comprehensive health insurance. Renewable annually, can lead to permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have German citizen or resident family members, family reunification visas provide a pathway. Requires proof of relationship, accommodation, and health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    EU/EEA citizens can move freely. After registering residence and demonstrating income, you'll enroll in German health insurance (GKV or PKV depending on circumstances).
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Health insurance is mandatory for all German residents. Requirements depend on your status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive coverage required before arrival</li>
    <li><strong>After residency:</strong> Must enroll in GKV or PKV within 3 months</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC for initial period; then German system enrollment</li>
    <li><strong>Income threshold:</strong> Above €69,300/year (2026) allows PKV option</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Germany</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Most senior expats start with international insurance for the visa, then evaluate GKV vs PKV after arrival. GKV offers predictable premiums (income-based) while PKV offers more choice but rising premiums with age. International coverage can supplement either system for travel and evacuation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors moving to Germany, these providers offer strong European coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Germany</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> German parent company, exceptional local network</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong European network, good direct billing</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Global:</strong> EU-regulated, competitive German pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Germany.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Germany vary significantly between international, public, and private options:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GKV if eligible:</strong> Income-based premiums cap your costs</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> €2,500-5,000 deductible reduces international premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Germany-only:</strong> If you won't travel much, local PKV may be more cost-effective</li>
    <li><strong>Annual payment:</strong> Most insurers offer 5-10% discount for annual payment</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving to Munich with $3,500/month pension. Wants access to German healthcare system.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care for visa application. After residency, evaluate PKV enrollment (income below threshold means GKV).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€400/month initially. GKV would be ~€500/month income-based.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, relocating to Berlin. One has diabetes.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with moratorium underwriting. Diabetes covered after 24-month exclusion. German GKV would cover pre-existing immediately.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€1,100/month combined for BUPA. GKV would be income-based.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Dutch Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EU citizen moving from Amsterdam to Düsseldorf for family.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Transfer Dutch coverage initially via EHIC, then enroll in German GKV system.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> GKV ~14.6% of pension income. Add international for travel back to Netherlands.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I join German public health insurance (GKV) as a retiree?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        It depends on your circumstances. If you've been publicly insured in the EU, you may be able to join GKV. If you've always been privately insured, you'll likely need to continue with private coverage. The rules are complex—consult a German insurance advisor.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is German necessary for healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        In major cities like Berlin, Munich, and Frankfurt, many doctors speak English. However, German significantly improves your experience and is often required for administrative processes. Hospital staff in smaller cities may have limited English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What happens to my PKV premiums as I age?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        PKV premiums increase with age and can become very expensive in later years (€800-1,500+/month for 80+). German PKV includes mandatory "aging reserves" to moderate increases, but it's still a concern for long-term planning.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does German healthcare quality compare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Germany ranks among the world's best for healthcare quality. Hospital infrastructure is excellent, specialist access is good, and wait times are generally reasonable. The dual GKV/PKV system provides options for different preferences and budgets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Germany.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with German authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
